# .env Guard — Never Break the Factory

When editing or reading `.env`, always verify these three lines exist
and are correct. If any are wrong, fix them immediately.

## Required lines

```
FACTORY_AGENT_PROVIDER_ORDER=codex,openai_api,deterministic
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...   (must be non-empty, valid OpenAI key)
EXECUTION_REPO_ROOT=    (must be empty — no external repo)
```

## Rules

- `FACTORY_AGENT_PROVIDER_ORDER` MUST include `openai_api` between
  `codex` and `deterministic`. Without it, agent runs silently fail
  to `deterministic` (no-op) when codex CLI is unavailable.
- `OPENAI_API_KEY` MUST be a valid, non-empty key. If it is empty,
  the `openai_api` provider fails and the factory does nothing useful.
- `EXECUTION_REPO_ROOT` MUST be empty. This repo is standalone.
  Setting it to the Arbitrage repo causes the dashboard to read stale
  data and show all portfolios as degraded.
- `EXECUTION_PORTFOLIO_STATE_ROOT` must be `data/portfolios` (local).
- Never remove or reorder these lines.
- Never commit `.env` to git (it is gitignored).
